<br>
Now, if this is true, does this mean that VI knows exactly what it is doing (making our taunt suck) , but yet offering a fix for it if you want to get to 59 or 60 and work your butt off even more getting AA to get AE taunt? Same thing really if you think about it, they just charge you more money every month while you work on the fix.<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
Now lets consider my theory regardless of anything thought of as the real way it works.<br>
<br>
I believe that hate lists are done on a point total and you get a varying amount of aggro per taunt, proc, spell, etc.<br>
<br>
I can support my theory by never being able to hold aggro through a slow with one taunt, however if I taunt something 3x, it won't think about going onto that shaman who I am grouped with.<br>
<br>
So to show a general view of my theory on how taunt works, here is a little more clear way of showing you it.<br>
------------------------------------------------------<br>
(Hate List)<br>
Main Tank-990 points<br>
Secondary Tank-600 points<br>
Cleric1-350 points<br>
Cleric2-350 points<br>
Cleric3-350 points<br>
Cleric4-350 points<br>
Shaman1-400 points<br>
Shaman2-200 points<br>
Enchanter1-400 points<br>
Melee1-300 points<br>
Melee2-650 points<br>
Melee3-330 points<br>
Melee4-290 points<br>
Melee5-360 points<br>
Melee6-250 points<br>
Melee7-250 points<br>
Melee8-250 points<br>
Melee9-250 points<br>
Melee10-250 points<br>
Nuker1-500 points<br>
Nuker2-500 points<br>
Nuker3-500 points<br>
Nuker4-500 points<br>
Nuker5-500 points<br>
Nuker6-500 points<br>
<br>
This would be assuming the max for hate is 1000. However I can't accurately say that as I haven't used an EB weapon and experienced a double proc with one.<br>
But back to my theory, certain actions during the fight would give an increase in aggro, such as the following.<br>
<br>
Melee damage=1 pt aggro<br>
Slow=500 pt aggro<br>
Tash= 500 pt aggro<br>
CH=300 pt aggro<br>
Nukes=damage/6<br>
Taunt=50-400 aggro<br>
<br>
Now with that in your mind, assume that every person loses 100 or 200 points of aggro per hit round for the mob. Hence how everyone doesn't max out.<br>
<br>
Notice that Melee2 has more aggro than the secondary tank, common to happen in most fights.<br>
<br>
Does 2 EB procs ( before recent bug)  back to back give you instant-aggro for atleast that turn of the mob's attacks?<br>
<br>
Doesn't a mob who is engaged summon a nuker but then go back onto the MT without touching the nuker many times? Was it right after a round of attacks that they were allowed to move away?<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
